VISUALIZATION
Converting data into charts so humans can understand quickly.
Types of visuals
1.	Comparison Visuals
2.	Composition Visuals       
3.	Trend Visuals
4.	Distribution Visuals
5.	Single Value Visuals
Comparison Visuals
This visual is used to compare values
Usage: Sales by category 
Ex: 1. Bar chart
       2. Column charts
1.	Bar chart
Which category has highest sales?
•	 Axis → Category 
•	Values → Sales 

 Composition Visuals
This visual is used to Show percentage / parts of whole
Ex: 1. Pie chart
2.	Donut chart 
1. PIE CHART
 What % each category contributes?
•	Legend → Category 
•	Values → Sales
Usage: Category contribution to total sales / Out of 100%, who has how much 

 Trend Visuals
This visual is used to show how data changes over time
Ex: 1. Line chart
       2. Area chart 
 1. LINE CHART
How sales change over time?
•	Axis → Date 
•	Values → Sales
Usage: Sales by Month / Is it increasing or decreasing
 Distribution Visuals
This is used to Show spread of data
Ex: 1. Scatter plot
       2. Histogram 
SCATTER PLOT
 more sales mean more profit?
•	X → Sales 
•	Y → Profit
Usage: Sales vs Profit / How data is spread
Single Value Visuals
This visual is used to Show one important number
Ex: 1. Card
       2. KPI (Key Performance Indicator)
Usage: Total Sales / Just show me the final number


Drill up and Drill down 
•	Drill down is nothing but going deeper 
•	Drill up is nothing but come back up from hierarchy
Ex: Google Maps:
•	Country → State → City 
 Zoom in = Drill Down
 Zoom out = Drill Up
Your data hierarchy:
 Year → Quarter → Month → Day
 Drillthrough 
go to another page with detailed data
Example:
 Click “Electronics” → go to another page → see full details








